Nanozooids regularly budded against basal lamina, in alternation with autozooids, at growing edge of colony. Peristomes shorter than, and diameter approximately one­fourth that of, autozooids. Nanozooids with one thin, colorless tentacle (devoid of cilia; 
Borg, 1926
) approximately half the length of autozooidal tentacles.

REMARKS: The resting position of the single tentacles of the reduced nanozooid polypides is horizontal with the colony surface, ex­ position (
Silèn and Harmelin, 1974
), interpreted as a surface­cleaning behavior.
